    {
      "id": "70929d80651934be75bcdd95a2e4f8b235775e45",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-03 07:14:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8b887df92ba5d7c60a0d6744201cfe8e6e9243c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-03 18:04:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nwhat happens if MDT (where master LFSCK is running) crashed just before the status file is updated? OST got their LFSCK instance running already? will they be \"leaked\" ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "59058ff174003ced86aa639a19a27c483e6c9937",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 01:21:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> what happens if MDT (where master LFSCK is running) crashed just before the status file is updated? OST got their LFSCK instance running already? will they be \"leaked\" ?\n\nThe LFSCK on OST will detect the LFSCK status on MDT periodically, although such period may be a bit long. So even if the MDT crashed, and failed to recover for a long time, the LFSCK on the OST can still exit finally.\n\nOn the other hand, this patch also fixed another \"reference leak\" on the LFSCK on the OST inside lfsck_layout_slave_double_scan(): if the LFSCK on the OST found its status become LF_INCOMPLETE some earlier, it may leave the double scan without releasing \"lfsck->li_double_scan_count\", that will cause the LFSCK to hung there for ever.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4efe08df26072f371ad48d85932379fde7f98aad",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 01:36:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nright, but what happens if MDT crashed and sysadmin restarted it right when MDT is back while OST is still running old instance?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0491b0cb7231284994f1b2dc0d86233c73527e1f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 01:49:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIf the MDT is restarted, then the LFSCK on the MDT will auto resume and skip orphan handling. Under such case, it will not care about whether the OST LFSCK is still run or not. The LFSCK instance on the OST will exit by itself.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "45781d724ba2423999a8ad33395634400d6e7168",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 01:53:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nno, it's a bit different case - MDT crashed and the status file isn't updated. then MDT restarts and sysadmin restarts LFSCK.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4d91586a5f922b44c7357c54fe76ffe773181271",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 01:56:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIf then, the sysadmin will get failure when he/she tries to start the LFSCK because the OST will tell the MDT that it has been already in some LFSCK. So the admin has to stop the LFSCK on the OST manually or wait it to exit for some time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d2ada42929299730439c3f6a4c536d7e83a4277d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 02:01:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nok. I guess there is some room for improvements here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1a9c3263f3441db12cfbdcea2dec94b600a377e9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-04 02:03:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMaybe, we have more things to consider in the LFSCK 5.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
